msgid "What goes here"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:51
#: 36155cdc62174fc6ac17ef89daeeadea
msgid "**Announcements**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:52
#: 7e145d202cee46e789fe061ab138635c
msgid "Announcement (read-only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:53
#: 2f7699cdad2a4bc6815b9185f6570411
msgid ""
"Release notes, API deprecations, scheduled breaking changes, community "
"events. Maintainer-posted. **Subscribe to this category** if you depend "
"on the library in production or in a paper."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:57
#: d3a80287768e42ce9f1b97a2c5ea0130
msgid "**Q&A**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:58
#: 97247e67673d470ba5567daaca8c905e
msgid "Q&A (with *Mark as answer*)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:59
#: 73784a10562c433e8856dbc16390d1ae
msgid ""
"Usage questions, install / environment problems, \"how do I do X with "
"TensorMesh\". The OP — or a maintainer — marks one reply as the accepted "
"answer, which makes the thread useful to the next person who hits the "
"same problem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:63
#: ad712960ca284c65b6fc39027aab008f
msgid "**Ideas & RFCs**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:64
#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:71
#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:77
#: 979b3082b9d8447984e24cac4b5c4922 d57d57402c404c75b09875ec50176e3c
#: d96357a7b6be4cc7bc172fd1d3a4d44e
msgid "Open discussion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:65
#: bac1aaea75a74967a05c513b5e40019b
msgid ""
"Proposals for new features, API design, breaking changes — *before* you "
"write the PR. Floating an idea here first usually saves a round of \"we'd"
" actually want this shaped differently\" review later. Link the eventual "
"issue / PR in a follow-up comment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:70
#: c9f324811865497094807e4326766056
msgid "**Show & Tell**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:72
#: 38d615700ae041beb948d87b4726172b
msgid ""
"Papers that used TensorMesh, simulation animations, blog posts, teaching "
"materials, comparison plots against other FEM stacks. Self-promotion is "
"welcome here — that's the whole point of the category."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:76
#: e9f611c9623644958b089f81419ce153
msgid "**General**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:78
#: e80481a61c54435a9d886f3d8a20fc69
msgid ""
"Anything FEM-, PyTorch-, or PDE-adjacent that doesn't fit above. Catch-"
"all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:83
#: 1e87e336b5224189971639d38999b4c4
msgid "Writing a good Q&A post"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:85
#: 765310da729246c5a1bb83edb3cd9398
msgid ""
"The same checklist from the Discord help-channel guide applies, and "
"matters even more here because future readers will arrive at your thread "
"via search — they only have what you wrote. See :ref:`asking-well` for "
"the full list. The short version:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:90
#: 0d24fad75e9a4f0e930c350b70dfd24a
msgid "**What you ran** — a minimal, copy-pasteable snippet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:91
#: 32562c1d2ce148eea432bad3d3242105
msgid "**What you saw** — the full traceback, in a code block."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:92
#: b1e5068fbd7d41d1a47947d87b2580b4
msgid "**What you expected** — shape, value, or behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:93
#: c9901d3d4ae1461c9584d51e5e57315f
msgid ""
"**Versions** — output of ``python -c \"import torch, torch_sla, "
"tensormesh; print(torch.__version__, torch_sla.__version__, "
"tensormesh.__version__)\"``, plus OS and CUDA version if relevant."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:97
#: eb93e5d10baa47e2b2f406d8e92789a6
msgid ""
"A useful habit: when the issue is resolved, **edit the OP** to add a one-"
"line \"Resolution:\" summary at the top, so future readers don't have to "
"scroll through the back-and-forth. Then mark the answering reply."
msgstr ""

