#: c7a98ad0ae0d48289f6f965f2fabf1f3
msgid "**Discussions → Announcements** (watch this category)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:130
#: 0e7edfd953e54dcb8661f49b6409638a
msgid ""
"When in doubt: post to Discussions, link from Discord. Chat that sounded "
"one-off often turns out to be useful to others later, and moving a "
"Discord exchange into a Discussion thread is a maintainer- friendly thing"
" to do."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:137
#: f078637a51f3418a94ab71a677a90a11
msgid "Labels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:139
#: aac4c7d1f389448ba3f72f2d07ac9129
msgid ""
"Maintainers may tag Q&A discussions with labels like ``installation``, "
"``cuda``, ``meshing``, ``assembly``, ``solver``, ``autograd``, or "
"``docs`` to make search filtering possible. You don't need to label your "
"own post — pick the right category, and the labels follow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:146
#: 5cbb4e9aa4064931bdf789adacb95b0e
msgid "Etiquette"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:148
#: 66664787f9a1451cb36df13921970550
msgid ""
"The same norms that apply on :ref:`Discord <etiquette>` apply here: be "
"kind, keep disagreements technical, no spam. A couple of Discussions-"
"specific courtesies on top:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:152
#: ce7d3610f2b54ca08508c059191799bc
msgid ""
"**Search before posting.** Many questions have already been asked. "
"GitHub's in-page search across Discussions is decent; a quick "
"``site:github.com/camlab-ethz/TensorMesh/discussions <your terms>`` on "
"Google is even better."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:156
#: ae27f0b40535493197d2b493819937a3
msgid ""
"**One topic per thread.** If you find yourself describing two unrelated "
"problems in the same post, split it. Threaded replies on Q&A only work "
"well when the question is single-shot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/community/github_discussions.rst:159
#: a101a36c4b824655ba36a5c260311208
msgid ""
"**Don't open a duplicate.** If your problem matches an existing thread, "
"comment there instead of opening a new one — even if the existing thread "
"is closed. A maintainer will reopen it or redirect."
msgstr ""

